texts.text: *This story ties into Chapter 12 of the Main Story.
>A great being is found peering into our world.
It seems that you made contact with [sys user_name], Astaroth.
Vanitas... The Extinction Event is nigh...
And the humans that hold the key to the future...
The denizens of the Netherworld will surely stand witness to their actions.
Yet we all bear some degree of animosity towards these humans.
Astaroth set that aside and made contact with [sys user_name]...
Insofar as establishing a contract with them...
[sys user_name] is a rather special existence in this world.
I do not know if this is God's will or not,
but there is no doubt that they are of paramount importance in terms of the fate of this world.
If Astaroth has taken into account what will happen after Vanitas,
and finds a way to control [sys user_name] then...
They may become a force that can stand up to even God himself.
[sys user_name]'s soul...
Has it been corrupted by Astaroth...?
And whether or not their Neo Liberators
And whether or not their Neo Liberators
have the power or capability to rise up against humanity's "malice"
is yet to be seen...
>In the Hideout, the Tokyo Branch members of the Neo Liberators have gathered.
Aight. Y'all got your drinks ready?
And... Happy...!
New Year!
New Year!!
>Everyone raises their glasses in celebration,
>and dig into the traditional New Year's spread that's been laid out.
This shrimp is enormous! Oh, and delicious...!
Yo, I ordered out so it's all on me. Enjoy!
Thank you very much. In that case...
Here's a plate and a pair of chopsticks.
Oh, thank you. That's very thoughtful.
Please excuse our indiscretion. We should be the ones doing that.
Don't worry about it! Let's just have fun today! Free and easy!
Oh my... This is amazing! I wish my family could have this too...
Hey, uh... If there's any left at the end, can I take it home?
I brought every container I could find in my house today!
Hey, don't hog it all.
But I guess it'd be a nice thing to do for them too.

*Snicker*
I want it all! Time to dig in!
J-Jeng Yun, why are you stripping? Are you already that drunk...?
It's a free and easy gathering, so I'm doing just that!
Wait, what?! Someone lied to you about what that means...!
You too, Vagit! Free and easy today!
I appreciate the offer but I will pass.
Arisa, let me get you a refill. If you'll lend me your glass...
Thank you... This is strange since I'm the one that's always serving the tea.
It's all on Megakin today, so it's okay to let loose.
Hey, wait! I wanted that one!
The early bird gets the worm! Mmm, so yummy!
>As everyone's fun conversations continue,
>you hear a mysterious voice whisper in your head...
Ah, so you are the ones that are to rise up against Vanitas.
Let us see if you have what it takes...
Yo, Newbie. What's up? Dig in!
I heard a voice...
You didn't hear that?
Voice? What voice? We bein' too loud?
Yeah, everyone's havin' a good time!
>A bright light envelopes your view,
>and you lose consciousness...
Thank goodness, you're awake. Are you okay, Newbie?
I'm okay.
Where am I?
Good. What a relief...
We're still keeping an eye on you, but at least you're back.
We're not sure either...
Seiran and the others are doing reconnaissance now.
>Seiran and the others return soon after.
Newbie, you're awake. You had us worried there.
Any news?
I took a look at the "chi" around here.
This definitely seems to be an Aura Gate...
But how could we have been sent here from the Hideout...?
We didn't do anything, right...?
The maid girl and priestess aren't here either...
Kazufumi and the priest guy too.
So the non-Dx2 Liberators aren't here at all...?
Seriously...?! Are the others okay?!
Hold up... Everyone, get ready!
Yo, what's up?!
There's something... Something bad is coming towards us!
>Just as Gakuto finishes,
>a thick, black pitch begins oozing out of the walls.
W-What is this...?! It's almost straight out of a horror film!
>It then begins morphing into what appears to be a spirit...
"This world should just disappear..."
"Everyone should be miserable..."
>The spirits begin spouting curses.
>These words reach everyone's ears,
>and you all begin to feel a sense of dread.
Ugh...! This is awful...!
Jesus... I feel like puking. Is it messing with our inner ears?
"Die. Everybody, die!"
I-I've never heard this kind of hate spouted right at me...
Yes. These voices feel incredibly evil...!
As if they only contain ill will or malice...!
Wait, does that mean this is humanity's "malice"...?
You may be right...
If everyone's malice were to flow into the Dragon Stream, for example...
It's more than possible that it could take on this sort of form.
Yikes! Yo, that means they're callin' forth Vanitas...!
This is what we actually gotta deal with?!
>The spirits hear the Liberators and attack all at once.
...!! They definitely seem hostile!
"Die!" "Everybody, die!" "Everybody, everywhere...!"
>As if to answer a summon, demons then begin to appear.
Shit! Demons too?!
Here they come! We just gotta get rid of them!
